tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (6.2%), indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible prediabetes. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of further evaluation or lifestyle intervention to prevent progression to diabetes. No evidence of renal or electrolyte disturbances.
